 behavior at lower T near the nematic quantum-critical-point. (iii)\nScaling relation of the specific heat jump at $T_c$, $\\Delta C/T_c \\propto\nT_c^b$ with $b \\sim 3$. (Note that b=0 in the BCS theory.) These results lead\nto a conclusion that the nematicity in FeSe is the bond+orbital order due to\nthe \"paramagnon interference mechanism\". The present theory paves the way for\nsolving various unconventional phase transition systems.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 4 May 2022 18:36:23 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 23 Jan 2023 15:10:41 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Thu, 2 Feb 2023 08:32:41 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-02-03"}
